==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tyrosin
<hw>Tyr"o*sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
cheese.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
nitrogenous substance<--amino acid--> present in small amount in the
pancreas and spleen, and formed in large quantity from the decomposition
of proteid matter by various means, -- as by pancreatic digestion, by
putrefaction as of cheese, by the action of boiling acids, etc.
Chemically, it consists of oxyphenol and amidopropionic acid, and by
decomposition yields oxybenzoic acid, or some other benzol
derivative.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>tyrosine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tyrotoxicon</ent>⟦br⟧
